Unchanged Impact to our thesis
Modest upside Financial results versus consensus
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research

S reported a strong FQ2, with ARR coming in well ahead of expectations, particularly after FQ1 was shy of expectations. FY26 outlook raised, but still embeds conservatism given company commentary. We remain on the sidelines given competitive pressures/margins, but did walk away encouraged.

A strong bounce back. After a rocky FQ1, where macro conditions had weighed on Net New ARR (NNARR), the FQ2 upside to NNARR was a positive surprise. While the quarter was particularly back- end loaded, a reason we didn't see more upside to revenue, we did walk away from the quarter encouraged. Reason being: 1) Seeing stronger breadth of platform adoption with \(\sim 50\%\) bookings from non- EDR products. 2) PurpleAI platform at the right place with need for AI security, experiencing triple digit YoY growth, a product that should improve with Prompt Security acquisition. 3) Flex pricing making product easier to consume, as we saw with 8- figure win during the quarter. We are still watching 1) Fiercely competitive environment around EDR and 2) Limited profitability pass through, but overall see stronger demand conditions for the company. We will monitor for how much Flex can help with core competitiveness of EDR market. Remain EW.

Strong ARR beat. SentinelOne delivered \(\) 1,001\$ mm in ARR (+24% YoY growth), ahead of consensus of \(+22\%\) YoY, a beat of \(\sim 160\) bps after a \(\sim 40\) bps miss in FQ1. The strength of NNARR of \(\) 53\$ mm was notable given it was up \(89\%\) QoQ. Given a back- end loaded quarter, revenue was in- line with expectations at \(\) 242\$ mm (+22% YoY). Seeing traction with broader platform, particularly around AI security. \(50\%\) of SentinelOne's bookings were from emerging products, showing greater platform adoption (Data, AI, Cloud). PurpleAI was particularly strong, growing triple digits, with attach rates \(>30\%\) , the highest level to date. Company believes that Flex should help further with platform adoption, removing one of the key hurdles to adoption. Flex seeing success in very early days. Flex is not even fully rolled out yet, but the company saw an 8- figure deal (renewal) during the quarter. The company expects that Flex should help with larger deals, and should help with broader platform adoption.

- FY guidance still embedding some conservatism. While FQ2 revenue was in-line with expectations, ARR beat was meaningful enough to drive more expected upside into the 2H. However, full year revenue estimates were really only raised \(\) 1.5\$ mm at the mid-point. The company talked to embedding conservatism after a particularly strong FQ2, but we would think there is more upside potential to the 2H.- Prompt Security acquisition. SentinelOne announced the acquisition of Prompt Security earlier in the month, helping enhance their AI security platform, particularly around AI-related data leakage. A key challenge with AI, we see this being a strong area of demand. The \(\) 180\$ mm acquisition is expected to be de minimus to FY26 revenue, but will provide an 80bps impact to full year margins. The deal is expected to close in FQ3.- Not yet significant profitability upside. While SentinelOne was able to post 2% operating margins, better than break-even expectations, the guide for the year called for 3% margins vs. 3-4% previously. As noted above, this is largely due to the Prompt Security acquisition. On FCF, SentinelOne reported a \(\) 7.1\$ mm outflow this quarter, worse than expectations from the back-end loaded quarter. Not expecting material upside to the year, but not meaningfully changing estimates.
